text=(:nogroupheader:)%0a(:Summary::)%0a(:Published::)%0a(:Author:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:License:[[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Res_communis|Site License]]:)%0a(:Update::)%0a(:Maintainer:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:Creator:[[]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!Cryptics]]:)%0a(:Also:none:)%0a(:Archive:[[|Archive.is]], [[|Archive.org]]:)%0a(:Download:[[{$FullName}?action=print|URL]],[[https://www.web2pdfconvert.com/|PDF from URL]]:)%0a%0aSee also [[Ergon fork]].%0a%0a!!Use cranepay code with following changes:%0a%0aUpdate yespower and change yespower parameters to require more memory.%0a%0aRemove max block size or replace with 1gb (ave tx size is 0.5kb [[https://bitcoinvisuals.com/chain-tx-size|#]] so 1 gb is 2,000,000 transactions so at 7.5 sec blocktime so 11,520 blocks per day so over 23B transactions per day compared to all US transactions at 100M [[https://www.cardrates.com/advice/number-of-credit-card-transactions-per-day-year/|#]]) also 80,000 times more than bitcoin.  Since bitcoin is sitting at 400,000 tx per day [[ https://bitcoinvisuals.com/chain-tx-day|#]] then this coin could do 24 billion per day with 80x faster blocktime and 1000x bigger blocksize, so the calculations check out.  This means everyone on earth currently could do 3 transactions a day on our network, which is plenty since we believe in competing blockchains.%0a%0aIntegrate ergon proportional block reward with doubling every 2.6 years (not sure what ergon is set to, probably 3 year doubling time) also increase coins emmited so that a median miner can earn 1 coin per hour.%0a%0aProbably need to change tx fee, target is 10 mins of mining can pay 1 kb transaction fee so about 0.1670 coins / kb.  This means for every minute of playing [[NatureVault.ProofOfPlay]], you would need to mine for 10 mins.  This means with 1 miner (PC) you can play for free for 2.4 hours a day.%0a%0a4 decimals only [[https://newmr.org/blog/how-many-significant-digits-should-you-display-in-your-presentation/|#]]%0a%0a7.5 second blocktime (for usefulness to [[NatureVault.ProofOfPlay]])%0a%0aTo every public key that sends a transaction in the block, the coinbase transaction pays them 0.0001 coins.  It costs 0.1670 coins to make a transaction so what is returned is negligible.  This is done in a [[CryptoProjects.BlockchainDesign#blocktock]] way to give an event that can be used as a token issuance under certain circumstances.%0a%0a%0a!!Important things not changed:%0a%0aDark gravity wave v3 (although digishield may be slightly better)
